                            <p>Golf Course Marshals have the authority to control speed of play and enforce all facility policies and procedures. In consideration of other players, marshals are authorized to control speed of play by requesting that players maintain the daily pace (i.e. skip a hole). Rochester Place Golf Club and Resort reserves the right to pair up groups for the purpose of speed of play.</p>

