                    <p>Hole 2 marks the course's first Par 5. For the majority of players, this is a true 3-shot hole, from the tips as well as from the front tees due to the presence of a creek 90 yards in front of the green. The tee shot requires some left-to-right movement to allow any chance of reaching the green in two, since a long, straight drive will likely find the grove of trees through the fairway. If you try to reach the green in two, the second shot must carry over the creek in an upward putting surface that typically features a back right corner pin.</p>
                    <hr>
                    <ul class="l-course_details">
                        <li><span>L</span> 471 YRDS</li>
                        <li><span>S</span> 515 YRDS</li>
                        <li><span>M</span> 533 YRDS </li>
