                    <p>A straight tee shot is a premium on this second hole to border the railway line, with out-of-bounds to the right and water along the left for most of the this near 400-yard hole. A flatter green approach can arrive high or be bumped-and-run to the green, although trouble abounds on the left as water continues in play and anything over the green presents a very difficult up and down.</p>
